{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Xcexd6zngPRie3deBnkRwG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The MongoDB StatefulSet doesn't use a ConfigMap. The mongod is started with just `--replSet mongodb-replica --bind_ip_all`. There's no `mongod.conf` file mounted.\n\nFor:\n1. **Logging verbosity** (logLevel) - can be changed at runtime via `db.adminCommand({setParameter: 1, logLevel: 2})`\n2. **slowms** - can be changed at runtime via `db.adminCommand({profile: 0, slowms: 400})`  \n3. **WiredTiger journal compression** - this is a storage engine setting that typically requires config file changes and a restart. \n\nThough in MongoDB 6.0+, I can use the `wiredTigerEngineRuntimeConfig` parameter to adjust some WiredTiger settings at runtime, including journal compression, without a full restart. I should verify whether the `wiredTigerEngineRuntimeConfig` parameter actually supports journal compression changes at runtime, since that would let me apply the setting immediately without a restart. If it does work, I can apply all three changes (logLevel, slowms, and journal compression) via `setParameter`, then update the StatefulSet command to ensure the settings persist across pod restarts. I can use `wiredTigerEngineRuntimeConfig` to apply the journal compression change at runtime, which MongoDB supports. So my approach is to apply all runtime changes (logLevel, slowms, and journal compression) to every member, then update the StatefulSet with the persistent `--wiredTigerJournalCompressor zlib` flag and trigger a rolling restart to ensure consistency across the cluster.\n\nBut I need to verify whether the runtime journal compression change actually persists to WiredTiger's storage or if it only affects new journal entries going forward. Let me check what the current journal compressor setting is.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1278,"cache_read_input_tokens":31684,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1278},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f72980e0-7b8c-4629-8faf-b859785029ae","uuid":"71986eb7-538c-4337-9030-626789052949","request_id":"req_011CcQCTEoWkZ2dkWELRd46B"}
